The paper deals with hyperspectral imaging, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves message passing and matrix factorization, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of prior parameters and model-order selection, which are topics in statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper includes numerical experiments with both synthetic and real-world data, which suggests a potential overlap with multimedia (cs.MM).
